ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_0: Has the story of Musa reached you:
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_1: Has the story of Moses come to you
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_3: (Muhammad), have you heard the story of Moses
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_4: Did the news of Moosa reach you?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_5: Has there come to you the story of Musa
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_6: Has not there come to you the story of Musa?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_7: Hast thou received the story of Moses?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_8: Hath there come unto thee the history of Moses?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_9: Have you heard the story of Moses?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_10: Hath there come Unto thee the story of Musa!
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_11: Did you receive the story of Moses,
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_12: Has the story of Moses reached thee?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_13: Has there come to you the story of Musa (Moses)?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_14: Have you received the story of Moses?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_15: Has the story of Moses reached you?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_16: Has there reached you the story of Moses? -
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_17: [79:15] Have you, O Muhammad (s), received the story of Moses (hadīthu Mūsā operates [the clause that follows]),
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_18: (Hath there come unto thee) Muhammad (the history of Moses) the story of Moses? Meaning: the story of Moses has already come to you; and it is also said this means: the story of Moses has not yet come to you.
